  "content": "\n# ADU & Casita Construction Guide for Arizona: Planning Your Guest House\n\nAccessory Dwelling Units (ADUs), commonly referred to in the Southwest as detached casitas or guest houses, represent a major growth sector in Arizona real estate. Building a casita in your backyard is a versatile option for adding high-end functional space to your property. It provides independent multigenerational housing for aging parents, a quiet and isolated professional home office, or a premium guest suite for visiting relatives.\n\nIn this comprehensive design-build guide, we break down everything you need to know about zoning regulations, utility hookups, permitting, and construction budgets for detached and attached casitas in the East Valley.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Zoning Codes & Plot Scoping for Arizona Casitas\n\nBefore launching architectural blueprints, the first step is analyzing your lot size and confirming zoning feasibility. In municipalities like the **City of Chandler**, zoning regulations define the footprint constraints of secondary structures:\n*   **Size Limits:** A detached ADU or casita cannot exceed 800 square feet or 50% of the primary dwelling's total square footage (whichever is smaller).\n*   **Height Restrictions:** Single-story units are typically capped at 15 feet to maintain privacy between neighboring yards.\n*   **Setbacks:** Detached casitas must be located in the rear half of the lot and maintain specific setback distances from property boundaries—typically 3 feet to 5 feet, depending on whether there are dry utilities or irrigation easements.\n*   **Architectural Harmony:** To satisfy building safety reviews and HOA requirements, the exterior design, stucco finishing, paint colors, and clay tile roof pitch of the casita must match the primary residence.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Utility Engineering: Sewer, Water, HVAC, & Electric\n\nConstructing a fully functional, livable secondary dwelling requires routing structural mechanicals:\n\n### Sewer Trenching & Slab Plumbing\nTo hook up a luxury bathroom and kitchenette, we saw-cut your yard and trench the subfloor to connect the casita's 3-inch plumbing lines directly into your home's main sewer stack. Tapping into concrete slabs requires precise slope angles to ensure correct code-compliant drainage.\n\n### Electrical Panel Upgrades\nAdding an independent casita with appliances, laundry connections, and climate control puts a significant load on your electrical system. We audit your home's main electrical panel. If your primary supply is 200-amps, we often run a dedicated 100-amp subpanel to the casita to handle the new load safely.\n\n### High-Efficiency Zone Cooling (HVAC)\nStandard central air systems cannot easily be extended to detached units. We specify and install ductless mini-split HVAC systems. Mini-splits are incredibly efficient, quiet, and offer independent climate zone control, ensuring guests or home office users stay comfortable in the summer heat without cooling underutilized spaces.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Average Construction Budgets & Timelines\n\nIn 2026, building a custom casita in Chandler ranges from **$55,000 to over $95,000+** based on structural specifications:\n\n| Project Scope | Average Cost Range | Construction Timeline |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Detached Casita Shell (Utilities Rough-In)** | $55,000 – $65,000 | 5 to 7 Weeks |\n| **Attached Suite Addition (Complete)** | $65,000 – $80,000 | 6 to 8 Weeks |\n| **Complete Detached ADU (Move-In Ready)** | $85,000 – $110,000+ | 8 to 12 Weeks |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Pulling Permits & Engineering Inspections\n\nBuilding an ADU is a complex structural addition that requires a comprehensive building permit from the local municipal planning office (such as the **City of Chandler Development Services Dept** located at 215 E Buffalo St). The process requires:\n*   Submitting civil plot plans, framing blueprints, soil safety checks, and mechanical schematics.\n*   Passing consecutive building inspections (footing inspection, concrete slab inspection, structural shear-wall inspection, mechanical rough-ins, thermal insulation insulation, and the final structural inspection).\n\nARZ Home Remodeling, operating under license **#ROC338304**, manages the entire design-build, permit acquisition, and municipal inspections process, providing complete peace of mind.\n\n---\n\n## Get a Professional Casita Consultation\n\nReady to add a custom casita to your Arizona property? At ARZ Home Remodeling, we deliver expert craftsmanship, fixed-price contracts, and a **2-year workmanship warranty** on all additions. Contact Mike Hernandez and our team today at **(520) 569-3339** to schedule your free, itemized layout evaluation.\n"
